Rating: 3
The first time I made this I used the suggestions for additional spices and brown sugar and used Egg Beaters instead of eggs. The bread came out well, but didn't keep well -- after a couple of days it was really soggy and starting to taste spoiled. This time around I made a few more changes, to lower the fat and try to decrease the sogginess. The bread came out great (my husband said even better this time), and I'm hoping that refrigerating it will help it keep longer. Here're the ingredients for my new version of the recipe: DRY - 1 3/4 c. flour; 1/2 c. brown sugar; 1 T. baking powder; 1/2 t. salt; 2 t. cinnamon; 1/2 t. nutmeg; 1/4 t. ground cloves. WET - 1/4 c. maple syrup; 2/3 c. orange juice; 1/6 c. (1/3 stick) melted unsalted butter; 1/2 c. Egg Beaters; 1 t. vanilla. FOLD IN - 2 medium Granny Smith apples, grated and pressed in a strainer to extract water; 1/2 c. chopped pecans.

