Rating: 3
Wonderful. I substituted walnuts for the pecans and Braeburns for the Golden Delicious since that's what I had on hand. I also added a bit of nutmeg and contrary to other experiences, this bread is nice and golden outside, moist on the inside. Be sure to follow the flour rules and don't scoop straight from the bag or pack the flour into the cup. Sift into your measuring cup, instead, or at the very least shake and pour from the bag, otherwise you'll get twice the flour you are going for. Anyway, the bread has a nice tang from the OJ and I'll capitalize on that next time by throwing in some cranberries, as suggested. Smells heavenly, too. This one's a keeper.

